        ("CRISPR-Cas9", "A molecular tool adapted from bacterial immune systems that allows precise cutting and editing of DNA at specific locations — the 'molecular scissors' that make gene drives technically possible by cutting the wild-type gene and forcing the cell to copy the drive sequence"),
