        ("PETase", "A naturally occurring enzyme discovered in the bacterium Ideonella sakaiensis that can break down PET plastic (polyethylene terephthalate) — the first known enzyme capable of degrading a synthetic polymer, now being engineered for enhanced activity"),
        ("Bioremediation", "The use of living organisms — bacteria, fungi, plants, or engineered microbes — to clean up environmental pollutants, including oil spills, heavy metals, pesticides, and increasingly, plastic waste")
