        ("Forest Carbon Sequestration", "The net rate at which global forests absorb CO2 from the atmosphere through photosynthesis minus the rate they release it through respiration, decomposition, and fire — currently forests absorb approximately 2.6 gigatons of CO2 per year, but this sink is declining as forests face heat stress, drought, fire, and deforestation", False),
